{"title_page": "Daniel Stashower", "text_new": "'''Daniel Stashower''' is an American author and editor of [[mystery fiction]] and historical nonfiction. He lives in Maryland.\n\n==Awards and honors==\nStashower has received awards and recognition for several of his works.\n\n===Fiction===\nThe mystery novel ''[[The Adventure of the Ectoplasmic Man]]'' was a 1986 Edgar Award nominee for best first novel.<ref>[http://www.theedgars.com/edgarsDB/ Edgar Award Winners and Nominees Database.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\nThe short story \"A Deliberate Form of Frenzy\" was nominated for the 1998 Agatha Award for best short story.<ref>[http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html Past Agatha Awards Winners and Nominees.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412020049/http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html |date=2010-04-12 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\n===Nonfiction===\n''Teller of Tales: The Life of Arthur Conan Doyle'' was the 1999 [[Agatha Award]] winner for best nonfiction,<ref>[http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html Past Agatha Awards Winners and Nominees.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412020049/http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html |date=2010-04-12 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> the 2000 [[Edgar Award]] winner for best critical/biographical work,<ref>[http://www.theedgars.com/edgarsDB/ Edgar Award Winners and Nominees Database.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> a 2000 [[Anthony Award]] nominee for best critical nonfiction work,<ref>[http://www.bouchercon.info/nominees.html#2000 2000 Anthony Award Nominees and Winners.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> and a 2000 [[Macavity Award]] nominee for best nonfiction.<ref>[http://www.mysteryreaders.org/macavity.html Macavity Awards.] Mystery Readers International. Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\n''The Beautiful Cigar Girl'' was a 2006 Agatha Award nominee for best nonfiction<ref>[http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html Past Agatha Awards Winners and Nominees.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412020049/http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html |date=2010-04-12 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> and a 2007 Edgar Award nominee for best fact crime.<ref>[http://www.theedgars.com/edgarsDB/ Edgar Award Winners and Nominees Database.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\n''Arthur Conan Doyle: A Life in Letters'' was the 2007 Agatha Award winner for best nonfiction,<ref>[http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html Past Agatha Awards Winners and Nominees.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100412020049/http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards_past.html |date=2010-04-12 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> the 2008 Edgar Award winner for best critical/biographical work,<ref>[http://www.theedgars.com/edgarsDB/ Edgar Award Winners and Nominees Database.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> and the 2008 Anthony Award winner for best critical work.<ref>[http://www.bouchercon.info/nominees.html#2008 2008 Anthony Award Nominees and Winners.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\n''The Hour of Peril'' was the 2013 Agatha Award winner for best nonfiction,<ref>[http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards.html Agatha Awards.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121111008/http://www.malicedomestic.org/agathaawards.html |date=2017-01-21 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> the 2014 Edgar Award winner for best fact crime,<ref>[http://www.theedgars.com/edgarsDB/ Edgar Award Winners and Nominees Database.] Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> a 2014 Anthony Award nominee for best critical or nonfiction work,<ref>[http://www.bouchercon.info/nominees.html Anthony Award Nominees and Winners.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120207060829/http://www.bouchercon.info/nominees.html |date=February 7, 2012 }} Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> was a [[New York Times best seller list|''New York Times'' best seller]] and editors' choice,<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2013-02-21/hardcover-nonfiction/list.html Best Sellers, Hardcover Nonfiction: February 21, 2013.] ''New York Times''. Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/24/books/review/editors-choice.html?_r=0 Editors' Choice.] ''New York Times'', 22 February 2013. Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref> and was on the ''Washington Post'''s list of Notable Nonfiction of 2013.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/notable-nonfiction-of-2013/2013/11/21/fdc4a820-35b4-11e3-8a0e-4e2cf80831fc_story.html Notable Nonfiction of 2013.] ''Washington Post'', 22 November 2013. Retrieved 2014-11-03.</ref>\n\n==Books==\n\n===Fiction===\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=1985 |title=[[The Adventure of the Ectoplasmic Man]] |publisher=[[William Morrow and Company]] }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=1989 |title=Elephants in the Distance |publisher=William Morrow }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=1998 |chapter=A Deliberate Form of Frenzy |editor1-last=Foxwell |editor1-first=Elizabeth |title=Malice Domestic 7 |publisher=Avon Books }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=1999 |title=The Dime Museum Murders: A Harry Houdini Mystery |url=https://archive.org/details/dimemuseummurder00dani |url-access=registration |publisher=Avon Books }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=2000 |title=The Floating Lady Murder: A Harry Houdini Mystery |url=https://archive.org/details/floatingladymurd00dani |url-access=registration |publisher=Avon Books }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stashower |first1=Daniel |year=2001 |title=The Houdini Specter: A Harry Houdini Mystery |publisher=Avon Books }}\n* {{cite book |year=2002 |editor1-last=Greenberg |editor1-first=Martin H. |editor1-link=Martin H. Greenberg |editor2-last=Lellenberg |editor2-first=Jon |editor3-last=Stashower |editor3-first=Daniel |title=Murder in Baker Street: New Tales of Sherlock Holmes |url=https://archive.org/details/murderinbakerstr00gree |url-access=regist